title: Westbrook leads Thunder to 113-102 victory over Jazz
text:
Westbrook scores 21 as Oklahoma City Thunder defeats the Utah Jazz 113-102 By KAREEM COPELAND AP Sports Writer   20, 2015 - 11:32 pmLast Updated: October 20, 2015 - 11:33 pm   
Utah (298) 

SALT LAKE CITY â€” Russell Westbrook scored 21 points as the Oklahoma City Thunder closed out their preseason with a 113-102 win over the Utah Jazz . The four-time All-Star had a triple-double with 10 rebounds and 10 assists. 
Rodney Hood led the Jazz with 23 off the bench. 
THUNDER: Serge Ibaka scored 16 on 7 for 14 shooting. ... Steven Adams finished with 14 points and 10 rebounds. 
JAZZ: Rudy Gobert stuggled throughout with five points, four rebounds and two blocks. He had a minus-23 plus-minus in the first half. ... Trey Burke put up 20 points despite a horrid first half. ... Gordon Hayward scored 18 points. 
STAR WATCH: Kevin Durant looked to be in midseason form. Durant scored 11 in the first quarter on 4 for 6 shooting from the field. He finished with 29. 
UP NEXT: The Jazz host the Nuggets for their final preseason game on Thursday. The Thunder host the Spurs in their regular season opener Nov. 28.
